ble after twin earthquakes in Venezuela. Rescuers, including international teams, painstakingly tunneled for over 100 hours, maintaining contact and providing sustenance. His survival, a beacon of hope amidst devastation, saw him emerge to a tearful reunion, offering immense relief to his family and a nation reeling from tragedy.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/dont-tell-my-wife-how-a-venezuelan-man-trapped-under-rubble-for-over-a-week-was-rescued-alive/articleshow/132152383.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/dont-tell-my-wife-how-a-venezuelan-man-trapped-under-rubble-for-over-a-week-was-rescued-alive/articleshow/132152383.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T10:32:55+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132152938,imgsize-1158814.cms"/></item></channel></rss>